						<summary>

						<p>Broken slab set up near the well in the compound of the Aṅkāḷamma temple.</p>						

						<p>This undated epigraph may be assingned to the 18th century, on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. It records the construction of a well provided with steps in front of the temple of Aṅkāḷamma. It states that the inscription was incised by <hi rend="italic">agasāli</hi> Śarabhaya of Talamuḍipi.</p>						

						</summary>
